1
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:39,159
How is it?

2
00:00:39,159 --> 00:00:40,039
The stuff is ready.

3
00:00:40,039 --> 00:00:40,920
Want to take a look?

4
00:00:41,159 --> 00:00:42,000
Let's look at the family genealogy first.

5
00:00:42,159 --> 00:00:42,960
Let's look at the family genealogy first.

6
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,640
Here.

7
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,159
Drink some hot water to warm up first.

8
00:00:46,799 --> 00:00:48,439
There must be important information in this family genealogy.

9
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,920
Otherwise, Bai Lingling wouldn't have

10
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:50,799
come to us at a time like this.

11
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:52,479
What do you mean by "a time like this"?

12
00:00:52,479 --> 00:00:54,399
Isn't she a wanted fugitive right now?

13
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,759
The most important thing for us right now

14
00:00:55,759 --> 00:00:57,439
is that before those people come knocking,

15
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,920
we find the information in this family genealogy.

16
00:01:00,439 --> 00:01:03,560
We've flipped through this family genealogy a million times.

17
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,079
It's just a family tree.

18
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:08,359
Besides recording the family's lineage,

19
00:01:08,439 --> 00:01:09,760
what else could it possibly have?

20
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,640
I beg to differ.

21
00:01:12,079 --> 00:01:14,319
Take Bai Lingling's family genealogy, for example.

22
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:15,560
It's very strange.

23
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:18,680
The way the names of ancestors and descendants are ordered

24
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:20,879
is completely different from a normal family genealogy.

25
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:24,000
And some names are marked in red.

26
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,480
There must be

27
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:26,760
something fishy going on here.

28
00:01:27,079 --> 00:01:27,879
Wait a minute.

29
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:29,040
Look at this.

30
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,000
The lines on these two pages

31
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:34,359
seem like they can be put together.

32
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:36,480
Let's take them apart and piece them together.

33
00:01:50,799 --> 00:01:51,599
Look here.

34
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:54,680
The holes and patterns on each page

35
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:56,840
look exactly like the Hanshan Jade Plaque.

36
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:01,439
Hanshan Jade Plaque?

37
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,719
What's that?

38
00:02:02,719 --> 00:02:04,200
This Hanshan Jade Plaque...

39
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,239
The circle divided into eight equal parts on its pattern

40
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:09,159
relates to the solstices, sunrise and sunset directions,

41
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:12,120
as well as the four seasons and eight festivals.

42
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:15,080
Also, there are holes around the edges.

43
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:16,199
The archaeological community infers

44
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:18,560
that the holes on the Hanshan Jade Plaque

45
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:21,680
might be the prototype of the Luoshu.

46
00:02:21,759 --> 00:02:22,800
This Luoshu

47
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,560
has nine numbers,

48
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,879
with five in the center.

49
00:02:30,319 --> 00:02:31,560
Look at the numbers on this.

50
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:33,400
Could this be the correct order

51
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,039
for the pages of the family genealogy?

52
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:36,120
Let me try.

53
00:02:44,639 --> 00:02:45,960
That's it.

54
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,240
Why is it arranged by the numbers of the Luoshu?

55
00:02:54,199 --> 00:02:54,800
Wait.

56
00:03:03,199 --> 00:03:05,560
The information this family genealogy wants to convey is...

57
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:06,319
Directions.

58
00:03:07,319 --> 00:03:08,039
Directions?

59
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:09,759
The two lines represent the north-south meridian

60
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,840
and the east-west parallel.

61
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,719
The four cardinal points are east, west, south, and north.

62
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:15,280
And the four hooks represent Chou and Yin in the northeast,

63
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,479
Chen and Si in the southeast,

64
00:03:16,479 --> 00:03:17,639
Wei and Shen in the southwest,

65
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:19,159
and Xu and Hai in the northwest,

66
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,680
corresponding to the four corners.

67
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,159
Then, if we combine the family genealogy with the map,

68
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:24,039
we'll find that

69
00:03:24,159 --> 00:03:24,879
the arrangement of the cities

70
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:27,199
exactly matches the name arrangement in the family genealogy.

71
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:28,960
Look.

72
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,240
After matching them up,

73
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,360
you'll find that three names are in red.

74
00:03:32,919 --> 00:03:36,639
Aren't those the Abyssal Ruins of the Desert and the Yunling Secret Realm?

75
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:37,759
Exactly.

76
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,080
It really is.

77
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:41,120
The third one is...

78
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:41,960
Fucheng.

79
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,759
Fucheng?

80
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:47,919
Old Chen!

81
00:03:47,919 --> 00:03:48,719
Chen Youxi!

82
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:50,680
Old Chen!

83
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,159
How is he?

84
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,240
Don't run, you bastard!

85
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:05,680
Be careful!

86
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,879
There's gasoline!

87
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,720
It suddenly exploded!

88
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,040
What happened? What happened?

89
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,519
Stop, stop. No one's around.

90
00:04:50,079 --> 00:04:51,839
Lao Lu, why are you still stuck there?

91
00:04:51,839 --> 00:04:52,839
You're even worse than me.

92
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:54,480
No one should be chasing us anymore, right?

93
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:57,439
We switched cars, so who the heck would chase us?

94
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,199
But this car isn't as comfortable as the other one.

95
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:01,519
It's giving me a backache.

96
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,600
Just be glad.

97
00:05:03,639 --> 00:05:06,680
If it weren't for Commander Chen's brilliant escape plan,

98
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,800
how could we have escaped the tiger's den?

99
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:10,519
I have an idea.

100
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,639
Rather than sitting around waiting to die,

101
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,040
we should take the offensive.

102
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:13,920
Lao Lu,

103
00:05:14,199 --> 00:05:15,399
quickly find a master forger.

104
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,399
Get the most reliable one.

105
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,040
Make a fake copy of that family genealogy.

106
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:18,639
Get it done as soon as possible.

107
00:05:18,639 --> 00:05:19,600
Meet up at my place.

108
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:19,839
Okay.

109
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:20,519
Fatty,

110
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:21,920
there are bulletproof vests under the car seats.

111
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,240
Take them out and have everyone put them on.

112
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,199
Where did you get these things?

113
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:27,000
I prepared them before we went to Yunling.

114
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,279
I forgot to bring them when we left.

115
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,439
Those guys are coming right for the family genealogy.

116
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:33,000
Old Chen!

117
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:33,720
Chen Youxi!

118
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,680
Fall back, fall back!

119
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,759
Help!

120
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,639
Help!

121
00:05:42,639 --> 00:05:43,879
Help!

122
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,439
We're gonna die!

123
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,240
Hurry up!

124
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,240
Help!

125
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,560
Do you have an axe?

126
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,040
We're not gonna make it!

127
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:56,480
I'm choking to death!

128
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,680
Help!

129
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,759
That sounded so fake.

130
00:06:00,199 --> 00:06:01,000
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

131
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,800
It just suddenly exploded!

132
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,720
What happened? What happened?

133
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:15,199
Why did it explode out of nowhere?

134
00:06:17,959 --> 00:06:18,879
Why do you think

135
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:20,600
Bai Lingling wants more than just the secret of the family genealogy?

136
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,000
Those guys were on the roof the whole time,

137
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,319
lying in ambush without making a move.

138
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,639
They attacked us right after we solved the puzzle.

139
00:06:25,639 --> 00:06:26,639
Isn't it obvious?

140
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:29,480
So they were just waiting there

141
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,160
to steal the fruits of our labor.

142
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,399
That's not right.

143
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:35,519
If they see the fake family genealogy,

144
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:37,399
won't they know we're lying?

145
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:39,000
Absolutely not.

146
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,839
I played a little trick on them.

147
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,959
There was a red name on the family genealogy,

148
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:45,639
and I moved it to a different spot.

149
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:46,360
So,

150
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:49,759
now they have to believe our conclusion.

151
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,279
Fucheng.

152
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:53,959
Lao Lu,

153
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:56,079
you finally did something reliable.

154
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:58,120
When have I ever been unreliable?

155
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:01,160
But based on what you three are saying,

156
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:03,959
this third place is connected to the Abyssal Ruins of the Desert

157
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,120
and Yunling.

158
00:07:06,199 --> 00:07:07,639
It seems this third place

159
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:09,399
should also be connected to the Lingxiao Pearl.

160
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:11,759
But where exactly is this third place?

161
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:15,560
Lao Lu,

162
00:07:15,839 --> 00:07:16,879
give me that family genealogy.

163
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,319
Look.

164
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,199
On the back of this family genealogy

165
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,879
is a topographical map.

166
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:28,399
What topographical map?

167
00:07:28,879 --> 00:07:30,480
"Water an inch higher is a mountain,

168
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,240
earth an inch lower is a winding stream.

169
00:07:32,279 --> 00:07:33,959
Yin and Yang dragons entwine and disturb each other.

170
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,079
Beautiful sand and water, a perfect layout."

171
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:39,000
Commander Chen,

172
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,480
what kind of jargon is this?

173
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,680
You never taught me this.

174
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,920
That means it's a feng shui treasure land for building a tomb.

175
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:45,560
I looked at that map.

176
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:47,240
It looks like a big toad with its mouth open.

177
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,560
And you call this a treasure land?

178
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:50,399
It is a bit crude,

179
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,040
but the terrain's layout is very clear.

180
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,959
What? What's clear?

181
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,680
Old Chen,

182
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,360
are you saying

183
00:08:00,199 --> 00:08:02,360
there's an ancient tomb there too?

184
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,600
I don't know if there's an ancient tomb,

185
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:06,319
but this third location

186
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,639
is right there.

187
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:11,279
Sounds to me like we're about to set off.

188
00:08:11,279 --> 00:08:12,439
Is that right?

189
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,639
Even if we do, no one said we're taking you.

190
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,759
What are you getting excited for?

191
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:17,000
Shut up.

192
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,879
It's not up to you whether I go or not.

193
00:08:18,879 --> 00:08:21,079
Old Chen calls the shots, right?

194
00:08:21,319 --> 00:08:22,439
When are we leaving?

195
00:08:22,959 --> 00:08:24,079
We leave at dawn.

196
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:11,559
Curator Zhu,

197
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:13,279
with your anti-reconnaissance skills,

198
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:15,080
you really should be transferred to the police station

199
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:16,639
to specifically fight criminals.

200
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,480
I immediately thought of contacting you then,

201
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,200
but your home phone wouldn't connect.

202
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,440
By the time I rushed to your house,

203
00:09:24,559 --> 00:09:26,240
it had already been burned down.

204
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,559
My intuition tells me

205
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,279
these two incidents must be connected.

206
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,759
Next month,

207
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,000
the Archaeological Research Institute

208
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:36,080
will hold a study seminar.

209
00:09:36,639 --> 00:09:39,120
The theme is the diversity of ancient China.

210
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:40,879
I hope you can bring your research

211
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:43,600
on Tang Dynasty relics to speak on stage,

212
00:09:44,039 --> 00:09:46,399
and discuss and exchange ideas

213
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:47,399
with scholars from all over the world.

214
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,000
If possible,

215
00:09:49,279 --> 00:09:51,320
you could give us a list of the artifacts.

216
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,440
It doesn't need to be too detailed,

217
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,720
just specifying the categories is fine.

218
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:57,000
Did the director of your institute

219
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,960
come along this time too?

220
00:09:58,279 --> 00:09:59,440
He didn't have time this time.

221
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:00,679
I'm just representing him.

222
00:10:03,159 --> 00:10:05,559
So this fake professor wanting the artifact list

223
00:10:06,279 --> 00:10:07,600
is also after the family genealogy.

224
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,399
It's possible.

225
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,480
They might think I handed the artifacts and the list

226
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,000
over to Old Zhu to handle together.

227
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,639
These guys aren't just watching us,

228
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:19,240
they're also targeting Old Zhu.

229
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:22,600
What exactly is the identity of this group you mentioned?

230
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:25,559
They're the ones who messed with us in Yunling.

231
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:26,679
They thought

232
00:10:26,679 --> 00:10:27,360
that by using us

233
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,600
to unlock the secrets in this family genealogy,

234
00:10:29,919 --> 00:10:30,879
they could then silence us.

235
00:10:30,879 --> 00:10:32,279
Isn't it just that simple?

236
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:32,960
What do you mean

237
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:35,440
they thought they used you to find the family genealogy's secret?

238
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,320
It's a long story.

239
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:38,200
Anyway, for now,

240
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,000
we should have shaken them off temporarily.

241
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,480
The real family genealogy is still in our hands,

242
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,039
and only we know the secret.

243
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:45,840
Xiao Chen,

244
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:49,960
I heard you're heading near the Jinghong River.

245
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:52,039
I found some materials before I came.

246
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,000
Take a look.

247
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:57,159
The Jinghong River has a tributary

248
00:10:57,159 --> 00:10:58,600
called the Shepazi River.

249
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,799
This tributary bypasses Mount Ailong

250
00:11:00,919 --> 00:11:02,600
and flows into a valley,

251
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,600
forming a ravine.

252
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:06,440
Because of its low elevation,

253
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:07,759
this ravine is shrouded in mist all year round.

254
00:11:07,759 --> 00:11:08,759
It breeds many insects,

255
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,320
so locals call it Guyu.

256
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,919
According to historical records,

257
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,360
in this Guyu,

258
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,960
there is indeed a mysterious ancient tomb

259
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,080
called the Tomb of the Dian King.

260
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,200
Records show that

261
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,080
a group of people in the ancient Dian Kingdom

262
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,600
believed in evil gods and sorcery.

263
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:22,759
To escape the war,

264
00:11:22,759 --> 00:11:23,960
they fled the Dian Kingdom

265
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,919
and migrated to the deep mountains near the Jinghong River.

266
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,159
The leader of this group was called the Dian King.

267
00:11:29,279 --> 00:11:30,200
Previously, we

268
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,919
also received some reports from the locals

269
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,360
and sent people to investigate,

270
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,080
but they were all abandoned mounds.

271
00:11:37,879 --> 00:11:39,639
Now we can basically conclude

272
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,360
that the real Tomb of the Dian King is in this area.

273
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:43,799
So what we need to do now

274
00:11:43,799 --> 00:11:45,240
is to cross Mount Ailong,

275
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,360
reach Guyu,

276
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:48,279
and look for the Tomb of the Dian King inside.

277
00:11:48,279 --> 00:11:49,000
Exactly.

278
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:49,919
A Tang Dynasty tomb

279
00:11:49,919 --> 00:11:50,919
and the Tomb of the Dian King.

280
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:53,120
They are far apart in both time and distance.

281
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,720
In two different civilizations,

282
00:11:54,759 --> 00:11:56,799
the exact same mark appeared.

283
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,600
It's truly amazing.

284
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:00,200
Therefore,

285
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,559
you must find

286
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:03,240
the potential connection between the two tombs.

287
00:12:03,399 --> 00:12:06,559
I think this will be another major discovery.

288
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:08,200
Listen to Curator Zhu.

289
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,519
I almost want to clap.

290
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,360
That sounds too grand.

291
00:12:11,559 --> 00:12:12,919
For us,

292
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,200
there is only one goal,

293
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,639
which is to break the curse on Old Chen.

294
00:12:17,159 --> 00:12:18,200
Fatty is right.

295
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:21,120
Little Chen, this is what I entrust to you as well.

296
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:23,759
Commander Chen,

297
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:26,759
look at all of us heroes here.

298
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,679
It's rare

299
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,519
to successfully join forces in the great southwest.

300
00:12:30,519 --> 00:12:31,399
Let's, let's, let's...

301
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,200
Well,

302
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:35,799
let's use this instead of alcohol, okay?

303
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,320
Give a speech.

304
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,120
Then you do it.

305
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,200
Wait, is it appropriate for me?

306
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,120
Comrades,

307
00:12:42,639 --> 00:12:43,440
tomorrow,

308
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,120
I,

309
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,759
Commander Chen, Staff Officer He,

310
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:47,960
and Lao Lu,

311
00:12:48,639 --> 00:12:50,720
will set off into the mountains together.

312
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,159
Say something inspiring.

313
00:12:52,159 --> 00:12:52,639
Okay, okay.

314
00:12:52,639 --> 00:12:53,200
Inspiring.

315
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:53,679
Inspiring.

316
00:12:53,679 --> 00:12:56,399
On this beautiful day,

317
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,960
today we sing with drinks in hand.

318
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,080
Raise a glass to praise...

319
00:13:01,919 --> 00:13:02,679
Praise...

320
00:13:04,759 --> 00:13:06,120
Praise the heroes!

321
00:13:17,919 --> 00:13:18,679
Driver,

322
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,559
are you driving to the foot of Mount Ailong?

323
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,360
Mount Ailong?

324
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:21,519
Yes.

325
00:13:21,519 --> 00:13:22,600
I'll be heading there in a bit.

326
00:13:25,159 --> 00:13:25,879
Let's go!

327
00:14:02,039 --> 00:14:03,200
Old Chen, look.

328
00:14:03,519 --> 00:14:04,679
The Jinghong River is right ahead.
